JAVA OOPS

ðŸŒŸ Classes and Objects
These two are the basic concepts of OOPS classes and objects, classes are the blur print for the objects and objects are real world entity implementation.

class Car {
    // class level variables
    statiic String type; // static
    // instance variables
    String model;
    String color;
    int speed;
    Car() { // default  constructor, BONUS - if you don't write explicitly, compiler will any which way insert it compile time

    }
    // parametrised constructor
    Car(String type, String model, String color) {
        this.type = type;
        this.model = model;
        this.color = color;
    }
    
    // methods
    int increaseSpeed(int increment) {
        this.speed = this.speed + increment;
        return this.speed;
    }
    
    // ...
}
